					<head>Perushim</head>
					<msContents class="lccn.loc.gov/sh85013597" rend="visible">
						<summary>Two supercommentaries on Abraham Ibn Ezra's commentary on the Pentateuch.</summary>
						<textLang mainLang="he">Hebrew</textLang>
						<msItem n="0" rend="visible" class="lccn.loc.gov/sh85013597">
							<locus from="1r" to="110v"/>
							<title xml:lang="he-Latn-x-lc">Perushim</title>
							<title xml:lang="he">פירושים</title>
							<msItem rend="v">
								<locus from="1a" to="45r"/>
								<title xml:lang="he-Latn-x-lc">Sefer megilat setarim</title>
								<title xml:lang="he">ספר מגלת סתרים</title>
								<author>
									<persName xml:lang="he-Latn-x-lc"> Shemuʾel Moṭoṭ</persName>
									<persName xml:lang="he">שמואל מוטוט</persName>
								</author>
								<listBibl>
									<bibl>
										<ref target="Motot_1553"/>
									</bibl>
								</listBibl>
								<note>
									<p>Contains several references to other commentators.</p>
									<p>Folio 76r contains a piece beginning: <q>מרובע מספר השם שהוא כ"ו עלה ת"רע"ו</q>.</p>
								</note>
							</msItem>
							<msItem rend="v">
								<locus from="45r" to="108v"/>
								<title xml:lang="he-Latn-x-lc">Sefer sod H' li-yereʼaṿ</title>
								<title xml:lang="he">סוד ה׳ ליראיו </title>
								<author>
									<persName xml:lang="he-Latn-x-lc">Ezra ben Shelomoh ben Gaṭinyo</persName>
									<persName xml:lang="he">עזרא בן שלומה בן גאטינייו</persName>
								</author>
								<note>
									<p>Quotes several rabbinic authorities, most often the so-called 'Perush Franco' on the commentary of Ibn Ezra.</p>
									<p>Contains a charm for travellers by Shemuʾel Romilly, folio 108v.</p>
								</note>
								<listBibl>
									<bibl>
										<ref target="Friedlander_1967" type="page">232-233</ref>.</bibl>
								</listBibl>
							</msItem>
						</msItem>
					</msContents>
					<physDesc rend="visible">
						<p>Paper codex, Italian cursive script, unpunctuated.</p>
						<objectDesc form="codex">
							<supportDesc material="chart">
								<support>Paper codex.</support>
								<extent rend="visible">110 folios <dimensions unit="mm" type="leaf">
										<height>243</height>
										<width>180</width>
									</dimensions>
									<dimensions type="written" unit="mm">
										<height>200</height>
										<width>122</width>
									</dimensions>
								</extent>
								<foliation>
									<p>110 folios (+ 3 unfoliated paper flyleaves at the beginning and at the end).</p>
								</foliation>
								<collation>
									<p>11 quires of 10 leaves each.</p>
									<p>Catchword on every verso.</p>
								</collation>
							</supportDesc>
							<layoutDesc>
								<layout columns="1 " ruledLines="28 36" writtenLines="28 36">
									<p>Several references to other commentaries supplied in the margins.</p>
									<p>4 blank pages between the end of the first and the beginning of the next treatise.</p>
									<p>Watermarks of a semi-crowned eagle, similar to Briquet no. 99 (volume I of <ref target="Briquet_1968" type="page">25</ref>), dated 1526.</p>
								</layout>
							</layoutDesc>
						</objectDesc>
